  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink276-kilavi">varaiyātu vantoḻukum talaimakaṉait tōḻi neruṅkic colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> What the confidante said to the hero who kept coming without marrying, having approached him.           
          
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink276">
<l>mantik kātalaṉ muṟimēy kaṭuvaṉ</l>
<l>ṟaṇkamaḻ naṟaikkoṭi koṇṭu viyalaṟaip</l>
<l>poṅka liḷamaḻai puṭaikku nāṭa</l>
<l>nayavā yāyiṉum varaintaṉai ceṉmō</l>
<l>kaṉmukai vēṅkai malaru</l>
<l>naṉmalai nāṭaṉ peṇṭeṉap paṭuttē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>O man from the land</l>
        <l rend="space indent2">where the monkey that grazes on shoots,</l>
        <l rend="indent2">the lover of the female monkey,</l>
        <l rend="indent2">taking a cool, fragrant creeper,</l>
        <l rend="indent2">pierces the young clouds that swell upon the wide rocks—</l>
        <l rend="space">even if you do not yearn for her,</l>
        <l> marry her and go,</l>
        <l>having made [people] call her</l>
        <l>the wife of the man from the land of the good mountain</l>
        <l>where the kino tree flowers [near] the mountain cave.</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
